cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new method for training generative models using autoencoders and maximum likelihood or variational autoencoder objectives. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The proposed method is evaluated on image datasets (CIFAR-10 and CelebA) and achieves state-of-the-art FID scores. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new approach to generative modeling using autoencoders and discusses its advantages over existing methods. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The proposed method involves training neural networks to match distributions in the latent space. 
- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper discusses the generation of images using generative models and evaluates the proposed method on image datasets.
